# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Foreman environment configuration
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values appropriate to your machine.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Game data location (Phase 1 — MCP server) ──────────────────────────────
# Foreman reads Satisfactory's machine-readable game data from `en-US.json`
# (found under `<game install>/CommunityResources/Docs/`). There are two ways to
# point Foreman at it; SATISFACTORY_DOCS_PATH takes priority if both are set.

# Option A (highest priority): full path directly to the docs file.
# Use this when the game files are not mounted at their usual location — for
# example on a headless VM where the file was copied across manually.
# SATISFACTORY_DOCS_PATH=/home/you/foreman/game-data/en-US.json

# Option B: the Satisfactory install root. Foreman appends
# `CommunityResources/Docs/en-US.json` (falling back to the pre-1.0 `Docs.json`).
# Example paths:
#   Steam  (Windows): C:/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamapps/common/Satisfactory
#   Epic   (Windows): C:/Program Files/Epic Games/SatisfactoryExperimental
#   Steam  (Linux):   /home/you/.steam/steam/steamapps/common/Satisfactory
# SATISFACTORY_GAME_DIR=/path/to/Satisfactory

# If neither variable is set, the MCP server starts with an empty dataset and
# logs a warning — it will not crash.

# ── MCP transport ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How the server exposes itself. Default is stdio (what Claude Desktop spawns);
# there is no network port in that mode. Set to 'http' to listen on a network
# port instead (Streamable HTTP). HTTP mode has NO authentication — keep it on a
# trusted localhost/LAN only.
# MCP_TRANSPORT=stdio          # 'stdio' (default) or 'http'
# MCP_HTTP_HOST=0.0.0.0        # bind host for http mode (0.0.0.0 = all interfaces)
# MCP_HTTP_PORT=8080           # port for http mode

# ── Anthropic API (Phase 2+ — not used by the Phase 1 MCP server) ───────────
# The foreman chat backend will proxy requests to the Anthropic API. Free-tier
# users supply their own key. Documented here so the file is complete.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
